      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRINCE AKEEM (7) grows a leg for rider Fry who has only missed a drum once in six steers and will be better with that first-up effort out of the way. Doesn't know how to run a bad race and looks the one they all have to run down. COLOURS OF AUTUMN (3) is a four-time winner over this distance range and will be rock-hard fit for this. Gets 2kg weight relief with the claim and can make her presence felt. The well-related TURBEAU (2) (half to G3 winner and 2xG2 placed Thames Court) is one from one over this track and trip and regular hoop Wiggins stays aboard. Top-three aspirations. ROUGE MOULIN (4) has placed six of eight over this trip and looks one for the exotics players. SWATOW (8) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.",
